==Description== <!--T:3-->

<!--T:4-->
The [[Image:Templater_ToleranceFrame.svg|32px]] '''Templater ToleranceFrame''' tool creates a tolerance frame or a datum frame as an SVG file and adds it to the selected view.

</translate>
[[Image: Templater_ToleranceFrame-01.png|300px]]
<translate>

{{Caption|Tolerance frames and datum frame with editable entries}}

==Usage== <!--T:5-->

<!--T:6-->
# Select a view or any geometry inside the view.
# There are several ways to invoke the tool.
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:Templater_ToleranceFrame.svg|16px]] Tolerance Frame}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|Templater → [[Image:Templater_ToleranceFrame.svg|16px]] Tolerance Frame}} option from the menu.
# The '''Feature frame settings''' task panel opens.
# Select a '''Tolerance Type''' for a tolerance frame, or type a single (upper case) letter for a datum frame.
# If a tolerance type was selected adjust the following values:
#: (they will be ignored for a datum frame)
#* Optionally edit the Tolerance value.
#* Optionally edit each datum field, leave empty if not needed and succeeding fields will be ignored.
# Click {{Button|Ok}} to close the task panel and finish the tool.
# A '''NewSymbol.svg''' file will be saved in the {{MenuCommand|.../Mod/Templater/Resources}} folder and added to the selected view as a new '''FeatureFrame''' object.
# Drag the FeatureFrame object to its final position.
# Optionally adjust its values by editing the {{PropertyData|Editable Texts}} property in the [[Property_View|Property View]]

===Task Panel===

</translate>
[[Image:Templater_ToleranceFrame-02.png|350px]]
<translate>

* '''Tolerance type''': Sets the tolerance symbol in the first cell of a tolerance frame, or the single letter in the only cell of a datum frame.
* '''Tolerance value''': Sets the tolerance value in the second cell (and offers some predefined entries to have the diameter symbol at hand).
* '''Datum1''': Sets the first datum marker in the third cell. Values in following cells will be ignored if empty.
* '''Datum2''': Sets the second datum marker in the fourth cell. A value in following cell will be ignored if empty.
* '''Datum3''': Sets the third datum marker in the fifth cell.

==Notes==

* The widths of the cells are calculated on creation and cannot be altered afterwards.
* All texts in the cells are editable, in contrast the tolerance synbols are hard coded svg elements and cannot neither be edited nor swapped.

